                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/2089: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-15T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 15, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 15—3:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>840. My 755, April 7, 4 p.m. Foreign Office has just informed me Italian reply
                    received to proposals for Greek food relief. Reply is in some detail and imposes
                    conditions, but Foreign Office feels it is on whole favorable and that there is
                    now open prospect of immediate progress. It was intimated in Italian reply that
                    German reply would be identical. Foreign Office will ask Mallet and me to meet
                    appropriate official tomorrow when details will be communicated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
